						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Denine wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What do you think about homebrew developed using Pirate mapper? I have Mapper 192 in my mind.I want to use it becasue of need for CHR RAM, and CHR ROM.Basicly it's MMC3 but with extra 4kb for CHR RAM.</div><br />TQROM is similar: MMC3, ROM at CHR banks 0-63, and RAM at CHR banks 64-71.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Dizzy games need to have CHR RAM(unless game have small number of items, or you want to waste a lot of CHR ROM) because of items.And I want CHR ROM because i can have some neat tricks(BG animations, "breaking" 256 tiles per screen limit etc.).</div>
<br />MMC3 with a 32 KiB CHR RAM can already be expressed in NES 2.0.</div>

